Over 1.2million people have fled Ukraine as Russia’s invasion of the country enters its tenth day. Many more will get the opportunity to leave today as humanitarian corridors open to let Mariupol and Volnovakha citizens to get to safety. But just hours later, Russian troops were accused of not paying attention to the ceasefire agreement. Despite rumours that he has fled Kyiv, Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky – who shared a video confirming he is still in the capital. In the video shared on his Instagram account last night, Zelensky said: ‘Every two days information comes out that I have fled somewhere — fled from Ukraine, from Kyiv, from my office. ‘As you can see, I am here in my place, Andriy Borisovich (Yermak) is here. Nobody has fled anywhere. Here, we are working. ‘We like jogging, but now we don’t have time for that, for various cardio exercises,’ he joked. Follow Metro.co.uk’s live rolling coverage as it happens.